&lt;p&gt;The Community Manager’s key objective is to concept and execute engagement strategies that aim to grow, strengthen and excite our growing community of players. This individual will be the hands-on owner of our community ecosystem, responsible for independently creating and managing content across all social media and Discord channels, with a specialized focus on Shooter or Anime-style Gacha games.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will build direct relationships with players by actively engaging in discussions and addressing player feedback, utilizing your deep understanding of these specific genres and their unique community cultures. By leveraging social media metrics and data analysis, the Community Manager will work to develop ways to acquire new players, retain existing players and positively impact overall sentiment. As the voice of our players, you will also work closely with cross-functional teams to surface trends and discuss opportunities for improvement. The ideal candidate is a versatile multi-tasker who can manage everything from content posting to community moderation and data reporting to provide the highest quality experience for our players.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[Responsibilities]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute social and community engagement initiatives across key communication channels (social media, website, forums)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, manage and cultivate relationships with community of players on various platforms such as social media, forums and Discord.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write engaging content to promote game updates, events and promotions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor player feedback, sentiment and trends and provide ongoing analysis and reporting to inform game development decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the cross-functional teams to identify and action core issues or opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[Qualifications]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of previous experience in a Community Management or similar role, preferably within the video games industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing / executing content strategy across social media and web platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Essential&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for games and a knowledge of the MMORPG ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in social media writing and best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal, problem solving and decision making skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to adapt to changes quickly, take initiative and “get things done” approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Desirable&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical and curious – interested in exploring new ways to communicate and measure engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic working knowledge of Adobe Photoshop&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior knowledge of NC games&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with video and streaming platforms, such as Twitch and YouTube&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Irvine, CA pay range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$55,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$80,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer Support Lead&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Irvine, CA (On-site) | &lt;strong&gt;Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Customer Support Lead to serve as our internal owner of customer support operations across multiple live-service titles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a senior individual contributor role responsible for managing and holding accountable our external CS vendor partners, ensuring consistent, high-quality support experiences for players across at least three active game titles. You will own the full support operation from SLA oversight and vendor performance to escalation handling, knowledge management, and player-facing support quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a seasoned CS professional who has operated in live-service gaming environments, understands the pace and complexity of managing player support at scale, and knows how to get results through vendor partners. You are organized, data-driven, and a clear communicator who can represent support needs both internally to leadership and externally to vendor partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vendor Management &amp;amp; Accountability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary NC America point of contact for all CS vendor partners, managing relationships across multiple titles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define, track, and enforce SLAs, KPIs, and quality benchmarks; hold vendors accountable to agreed performance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular vendor reviews, provide structured feedback, and drive continuous improvement across support operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and escalate vendor performance risks proactively, partnering with internal stakeholders to resolve gaps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Player Support Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end support experience for players across titles, ensuring quality and consistency regardless of which vendor handles the queue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor ticket volume, queue health, and response times; surface trends and flag emerging issues before they become player-facing crises.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage player escalations, including VIP and high-visibility cases, ensuring they are handled with appropriate urgency and care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the internal escalation path when vendor teams need guidance on complex, sensitive, or precedent-setting support cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge Base &amp;amp; Support Infrastructure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain a centralized knowledge base, macro library, and response guidelines used by vendor agents across all titles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with game teams to keep support content current with patches, live events, and known issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop onboarding and training resources for vendor agents to ensure consistent quality and brand voice across all support interactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and recommend tooling, workflows, and process improvements that scale across a multi-title operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Community, Live Operations, and Product teams to align on player issues, known bugs, and support priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate support data and player feedback into actionable insights for internal stakeholders and leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate occasionally with NC’s development teams in Korea to share support trends, localization needs, or title-specific escalations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the voice of the play

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About NCSOFT America&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NCSOFT America is seeking an Executive Interpreter to support clear, accurate, and confidential communication between Korean- and English-speaking stakeholders. This role will primarily focus on real-time interpretation in executive meetings and business-critical discussions, while also supporting translation and light project coordination needs across the organization as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The executive interpreter will participate directly in executive meetings and business-critical discussions to provide real-time Korean-English interpretation, ensuring that tone, intent, context, and nuance are accurately conveyed. This role requires strong business acumen, sound judgment, and the ability to support confidential internal discussions that inform business decisions. The primary focus of the position is to enable clear, effective, and immediate communication during live executive and cross-functional meetings, rather than serving as a primarily written translation role. The ideal candidate will be comfortable working in a fast-paced gaming environment, understanding gaming terminology and business context, and bring experience supporting executive-level interpretation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide accurate, timely, and context-aware Korean-English interpretation during executive meetings, business reviews, strategic discussions, and other stakeholder communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support simultaneous or near-simultaneous interpretation for sensitive, confidential, and business-critical conversations with discretion, professionalism, and sound judgment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help Korean- and English-speaking stakeholders understand not only the language, but also the business implications, decision points, risks, priorities, and cultural nuance behind the discussion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate written materials as needed, including meeting notes, presentations, emails, internal documents, follow-up items, and other business communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist leadership, cross-functional teams, and multiple stakeholders with interpretation and translation needs across both formal and informal settings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately interpret gaming-related terminology, product discussions, development concepts, publishing topics, localization, live operations, monetization, operational updates, and cultural nuance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capture, clarify, and summarize key meeting takeaways, decisions, action items, and follow-ups when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide light project coordination or PM support, including scheduling assistance, action item tracking, follow-up coordination, and team alignment support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help bridge communication between Korean- and English-speaking teams by ensuring tone, intent, context, and business meaning are clearly conveyed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in Korean and English, with strong verbal communication, listening, and comprehension skills in both languages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience providing live interpretation in business meetings, executive discussions, cross-functional meetings, or similar professional settings; executive interpretation or translation experience is strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to provide simultaneous or near-simultaneous interpretation with accuracy, composure, and awareness of business context.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong business acumen and the ability to understand how discussions, terminology, priorities, and decisions connect to broader business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to interpret

