&lt;li&gt;Act as a technically fluent publishing producer who can identify, prioritize, and drive resolution of production, service, and Live Ops issues in close partnership with development, platform, QA, and operations teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee Live Ops at both strategic and operational levels, with a focus on service stability, rapid incident response, issue escalation, content readiness, and continuous optimization of retention, monetization, and engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business, player, and operational needs into clear production requirements, helping technical and cross-functional teams make timely decisions during live service situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own production schedules, milestone tracking, issue follow-up, and cross-functional coordination to ensure timely and scope-accurate delivery across publishing initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify risks early across development, publishing, and live operations, and implement practical mitigation plans to reduce player impact and business disruption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive major updates, events, hotfixes, and lifecycle initiatives, ensuring seamless execution and alignment with global content roadmaps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve publishing and Live Ops workflows by establishing scalable processes, reporting structures, escalation paths, and communication frameworks for fast-moving service environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with data, marketing, platform, QA, community, and development teams to ensure cohesive execution and high-quality player experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present KPI trends, incident learnings, production risks, and actionable recommendations to leadership in a clear and practical manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage external partners or development studios as needed, ensuring alignment with product goals, service standards, and delivery expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent NC America’s publishing, Live Ops, and technical service needs within global planning and decision-making discussions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a culture of accountability, ownership, urgency, and continuous improvement across publishing and Live Ops functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in game production, publishing, Live Ops, or technical program/production management, preferably for online or live service titles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to operate in fast-paced live service environments and respond quickly to production, service, player-facing, or technical issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of the North American game market, player expectations, platform requirements, and live service operating conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working directly with development, engineering, platform, QA, and operations teams to diagnose issues, define priorities, and drive practical solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
