&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Community Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Irvine, CA (On-site) |&lt;strong&gt; Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Senior Community Manager to serve as the primary voice and champion of our players for an upcoming FPS open-world shooter MMO.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this senior individual contributor role, you will set the standard for community strategy and serve as the lead CM, working alongside a team of Community Managers to shape how we engage, retain, and grow our player base. You will act as the critical bridge between our Western community and the development team in Korea, ensuring that player sentiment, feedback, and culture are represented at the highest levels. As the voice of our players, you will also work closely with cross-functional teams to surface trends and discuss opportunities for improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires someone who is as comfortable analyzing community data as they are going live on stream. You are a genuine FPS enthusiast, a natural communicator, and someone who thrives in a live-service environment where things move fast.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Strategy &amp;amp; Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead community strategy across Discord, Reddit, and social media channels, setting the tone and standards for the entire CM team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the de facto lead CM, mentoring and guiding fellow Community Managers while remaining a hands-on contributor yourself.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute community programs, events, and initiatives that drive engagement, retention, and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own community health metrics and report regularly on trends, sentiment, and opportunities to leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Player Engagement &amp;amp; Channel Ownership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and moderate our Discord server and Reddit community, fostering a welcoming and active player environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the social media team with community-driven content, amplification, and player spotlights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build authentic relationships with players, community leaders, content creators, and influencers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the community in live-service moments: patch launches, seasonal events, crises, and major announcements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Player-Facing Content &amp;amp; Streaming&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Appear on-camera for live streams, developer Q&amp;amp;As, community events, and team videos. Must be comfortable engaging players in front of an audience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with marketing and creative teams on community-facing content that feels authentic to players.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create written content including patch notes summaries, community updates, FAQs, and forum posts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Cultural Collaboration with Korea Dev Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the voice of the Western community to the development team in Seoul: Synthesizing feedback, sentiment, and player needs into clear, actionable reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Korean counterparts to coordinate community initiatives, localize messaging, and bridge cultural gaps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate cross-time-zone communication effectively, representing community priorities in product and roadmap discussions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
